This paper discusses the role of artificial neural networks in natural language processing and cognitive modeling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the architecture of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the past tense debate, which involves linguistic theory, and could potentially fall under the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
